## How to Use

| Command      | Shortcut | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| `kva2a`     | `ka`     | Convert kVA to Amps (prompts: kVA, Voltage, Phase) |
| `a2kw`      | `ak`     | Convert Amps to kW (prompts: Amps, Voltage, Phase, PF) |
| `kw2a`      | `ka2`    | Convert kW to Amps |
| `kw2kva`    | `kk`     | Convert kW to kVA |
| `kva2kw`    | `kw`     | Convert kVA to kW |
| `sizing`    | `size`   | Generator sizing: enter loads in Watts, get recommended kVA |
| `help`      | `h`      | Show all commands |
| `exit`      | `q`      | Quit |

### Examples

```text
⚡> kva2a
Enter kVA: 100
Enter Voltage (V): 400
Enter Phase (1 or 3): 3
```

You can also type all arguments in one line:

```text
⚡> kva2a 100 400 3
```

The conversation table will show:

```
+-----------+--------------------------------------------------+
| Speaker   | Message                                          |
+===========+==================================================+
| User      | kva2a 100 400 3                                  |
+-----------+--------------------------------------------------+
| Assistant | 100 kVA at 400V 3-phase = 144.34 Amps           |
+-----------+--------------------------------------------------+
```

### Generator Sizing

```text
⚡> sizing
Enter each load in Watts. Type 'done' when finished.
Load #1: 5000
Load #2: 3000
Load #3: done
```

The assistant will recommend a generator kVA size with a 25% safety margin.

